text: Movie Studios, Movie Trailer Makers: Take note: This is how you make a trailer. You tease. You show who is in it, what type of movie it is, and the most basic of a premise: The Set-up. And you end with a question- not the answer. You leave a sense of mystery. Liam asks a question. And the answer given by Vera is vague. Do not give a summarization of an entire movie. Or all the plot points. Less is More. Give just enough. I've never watched this film but came here because I was skimming through Amazon Prime, but they didn't have a trailer posted with it. It's a basic entertainment movie. A thriller- and I will check it out, but I'd be pissed if the trailer gave any more and doing so would've decreased my interest in watching it. Got it Trailer-makers?
